## AI Calls

All AI calls use `model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6'`. All calls go through `throttledFetch()`. All responses parsed via `safeParseJSON()`. Token usage from every response is recorded by `recordUsage()` for the budget tracker.

**Setup generation:**
- `generateSetting()` ŌĆö generates full setting object from user input or pool entry. Handles refusals by sanitizing seed and retrying.
- `generateChar(i)` ŌĆö generates one character. Injects OCEAN profile + wound territory. Uses `generatedSetting` for world context. Per-slot World toggle grounds user-described characters in setting naming/register.
- `generateConflict()` ŌĆö generates conflict seed from setting + optional conflict note. Produces `label`, `domain`, `environment`, `gatheringPremise`, `pressure`. Does not receive character data ŌĆö conflict is generated before characters exist in the drama.
- `generateAllRelationships()` ŌĆö generates all 10 relationships. Max tokens: 2000.

**Simulation generation:**
- `generateResidue(a, b)` ŌĆö core connection handler. Threshold framing in user message. Builds rich context from character profiles, relationship ledger, facet plan, established facts, charBeats, tension values, pressure arc.
- `performEventRewrite(eventNode, otherNode)` ŌĆö rewrites event in place. Object-passing prohibition injected. Stage 2 must deposit forward pressure in `friction` field.
- `generateSequentialEvent(idx)` ŌĆö generates events 1/2/3 during play. Event 1 receives conflict `input` directly. Events 2 and 3 use fixed escalation/irreversible instructions with object-passing prohibition. All events receive full simulation state (charBeats, establishedFacts, residue observations).
- `generateConflictReveal(n)` ŌĆö three progressive reveals.
- `generateStoryBeat()` ŌĆö periodic plain-language log entry (under 25 words).
- `generateTestimony(charNd)` ŌĆö character's biased account to mediator. Receives character stakes instruction instead of gatheringRoles.
- `generateIntervention(type, targetNd, playerText)` ŌĆö mediator intervention residue. Three types (Ask/Name/Propose).
- `openChallengeOverlay()` ŌĆö final challenge scene. Receives `pressure` field instead of `firstQuestion` in synthesis inputs.

